:"/docs/changelog-0","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog","content":"What's new?"},"3":{"id":"/docs/changelog-1","page_id":"/docs/changelog","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"v0.5.0"},"4":{"id":"/docs/changelog-2","page_id":"/docs/changelog","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/changelog#023","content":"0.2.3"},"5":{"id":"/docs/changelog-3","page_id":"/docs/changelog","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/changelog#022","content":"0.2.2"},"6":{"id":"/docs/changelog-4","page_id":"/docs/changelog","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/changelog#021","content":"0.2.1"},"7":{"id":"/docs/changelog-5","page_id":"/docs/changelog","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/changelog#020","content":"0.2.0"},"8":{"id":"/docs/changelog-6","page_id":"/docs/changelog","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/changelog#019","content":"0.1.9"},"9":{"id":"/docs/changelog-7","page_id":"/docs/changelog","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/changelog#018","content":"0.1.8"},"10":{"id":"/docs/changelog-8","page_id":"/docs/changelog","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/changelog#017","content":"0.1.7"},"11":{"id":"/docs/changelog-9","page_id":"/docs/changelog","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/changelog#016","content":"0.1.6"},"12":{"id":"/docs/changelog-10","page_id":"/docs/changelog","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/changelog#011","content":"0.1.1"},"13":{"id":"/docs/changelog-11","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"Major"},"14":{"id":"/docs/changelog-12","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"Update!"},"15":{"id":"/docs/changelog-13","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"This is the biggest update yet by far. The entire library has been migrated to a monorepo structure with scoped packages, allowing for framework specific exports, additional optimizations, and more! Framework specific exports is also the next big feature I'm working on."},"16":{"id":"/docs/changelog-14","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"As such, the name of the package has changed, gone is `toomanycharts` and in is `@jgmc/...`!"},"17":{"id":"/docs/changelog-15","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"Previously all functionality lived under `toomanycharts`, but now the math & framework agnostic code lives in `@jgmc/core`. Additionally I had one single dependency in-use for creating charts `linkedom` which is a fantastic library, but as part of this move I've removed it & am now just using strings!"},"18":{"id":"/docs/changelog-16","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"This has allowed for a `3x` speed increase, a smaller bundle size, and means aside from the `@jgmc/core` package there are now zero dependencies! Additionally strings are incredibly flexible, so right out of the box `@jgmc/vanilla` is completely SSR compatible, and can technically be used anywhere you can use a string!"},"19":{"id":"/docs/changelog-17","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"That being said framework specific exports are still on the way, so that framework strengths can be properly utilized, but in the meantime you can use `@jgmc/vanilla` in any framework, and it's already SSR compatible!"},"20":{"id":"/docs/changelog-18","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"Not only that but aside from a few exceptions, everything should work pretty much the same in terms of usage, aside from the output."},"21":{"id":"/docs/changelog-19","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"installation moved!"},"22":{"id":"/docs/changelog-20","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"`toomanycharts` is now `@jgmc/vanilla`"},"23":{"id":"/docs/changelog-21","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"`@jgmc/core` for math & framework agnostic code"},"24":{"id":"/docs/changelog-22","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"removed `linkedom` dependency, now just using strings for charts"},"25":{"id":"/docs/changelog-23","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"all charts under `@jgmc/vanilla` return strings"},"26":{"id":"/docs/changelog-24","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#023","content":"Removed `classes` option from all charts"},"27":{"id":"/docs/changelog-25","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#023","content":"replacing with sensible default classes applied to chart elements"},"28":{"id":"/docs/changelog-26","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#023","content":"See Charts Classes for more info"},"29":{"id":"/docs/changelog-27","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#022","content":"After a long break I came back and finished up the initial implementation of the `asciiBarchart` I'd been working on. While I plan to continue with ASCII chart types I felt there was still plenty more worthwhile things to add in to SVG charts. The big one being two very common chart types - pie & donut charts! Those have both been added."},"30":{"id":"/docs/changelog-28","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#022","content":"Next up I will be doing some cleanup / refinement of the codebase. Standardizing some things across chart types, doing some type naming adjustments, etc... You can check the `TODO.md` in the repo for specifics."},"31":{"id":"/docs/changelog-29","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#022","content":"After cleanup & refinement I'll be doing work on getting framework specific exports working."},"32":{"id":"/docs/changelog-30","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#022","content":"`piechart`"},"33":{"id":"/docs/changelog-31","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#022","content":"`donutchart`"},"34":{"id":"/docs/changelog-32","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#022","content":"Experimental features are features that are in the early stages of development, and may be subject to change or removal without a major version bump."},"35":{"id":"/docs/changelog-33","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#022","content":"`asciiBarchart`"},"36":{"id":"/docs/changelog-34","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#021","content":"`colors` is now `fillColors`"},"37":{"id":"/docs/changelog-35","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#021","content":"Added `strokeColors` to `barchart` and `barchartStacked`"},"38":{"id":"/docs/changelog-36","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#021","content":"Added `strokeWidths` to `barchart` and `barchartStacked`"},"39":{"id":"/docs/changelog-37","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#020","content":"Revamped labeling system:"},"40":{"id":"/docs/changelog-38","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#020","content":"dataLabels: 'literal' or 'percentage' for automatic value / percentage labels on bars"},"41":{"id":"/docs/changelog-39","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#020","content":"imageLabels: supply images (with optional topText / bottomText) for bar and line charts"},"42":{"id":"/docs/change