two colors like above results in stops like so:"},"262":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples-24","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples#gradients","content":"The nice thing is that any valid CSS color should work, here's an example using `oklch` instead:"},"263":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples-25","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples#gradients","content":"And another thing I added that I think is pretty cool is having a continuous gradient that's created with a bit of masking!"},"264":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples-26","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples#gradients","content":"To do this the `gradientMode` should be `\"continuos\"` & the `gradientDirection` can be whatever way you want it, here I've set it to match the top-side bar placement."},"265":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples-27","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples#animation","content":"Because JGMC outputs SVG strings that you can instantly turn into a valid SVG element, they can be animated! The caveat is that to animate the individual bars, depending on what sort of animation you want to do, you'll need to change the `transform-origin` for bars after the charts created based on which side they're on. Which sounds more complicated than it is!"},"266":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples-28","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples#animejs","content":"Let's look at an example, where to have the bars 'grow in' we'll need to do exactly that. I'll use my animation engine lib of choice -  animejs !"},"267":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples-29","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples#animejs","content":"Results in:"},"268":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples-30","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples#breakdown","content":"`main.ts` is just appending the chart to the page."},"269":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples-31","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples#breakdown","content":"`script.ts` does a few things, here's a commented version of it:"},"270":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples-32","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples#breakdown","content":"You may have noticed that there's a bit of a 'flicker' above - this is a known issue. It happens because the order of things as it currently stands, which goes something like:"},"271":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples-33","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples#breakdown","content":"Page loads"},"272":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples-34","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples#breakdown","content":"Chart created, added to page"},"273":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples-35","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples#breakdown","content":"At this point it looks normal with all bars full-width"},"274":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples-36","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples#breakdown","content":"`100ms` after, `scaleX` set to `0` so now the bars are suddenly gone, causing a flicker"},"275":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples-37","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples#breakdown","content":"The fix here is simple, and coming soon. I will add a `barStyle` option which will allow you to set inline styles for each bar, which'll get tacked onto them - avoiding the flicker."},"276":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples-38","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples#breakdown","content":"All that being said, the `transform-origin` is only relevant when you're moving the bars in some way, something like `opacity` or `fill` wouldn't require that at all."},"277":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples-39","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples#transformorigin-guide","content":"Regardless, here's a table & visual guide for all placement options!"},"278":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples-40","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples#transformorigin-guide","content":"placement"},"279":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples-41","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples#transformorigin-guide","content":"`transformOrigin` keywords"},"280":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples-42","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples#transformorigin-guide","content":"\"top\""},"281":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples-43","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples#transformorigin-guide","content":"\"top center\""},"282":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples-44","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples#transformorigin-guide","content":"\"right\""},"283":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples-45","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchart-examples#tran