 apart. Though this can be mitigated with CSS!"},"308":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchartstacked-examples-19","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchartstacked-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchartstacked-examples#gradients","content":"Of course that's not the only way of using CSS to differentiate the segments:"},"309":{"id":"/docs/examples/barchartstacked-examples-20","page_id":"/docs/examples/barchartstacked-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/barchartstacked-examples#animation","content":"To be filled in, though the idea would be the same as barcharts - except you'd need to stagger the animation & delay it so that they play in sequence per-segment. Unless you want each bar appearing at once then it's identical."},"310":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","type":"page","content":"Donutchart Examples","breadcrumbs":["The Lib","Usage","Charts Examples"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples"},"311":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-0","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","content":"A cup of coffee and a donut, anyone?"},"312":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-1","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#donutchart","content":"`donutchart`"},"313":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-2","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#quick-start","content":"Quick Start"},"314":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-3","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#label-options","content":"Label Options"},"315":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-4","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#data-labels","content":"Data Labels"},"316":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-5","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#center-label","content":"Center Label"},"317":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-6","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#styling","content":"Styling"},"318":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-7","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#size--spacing","content":"Size & Spacing"},"319":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-8","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#coloring","content":"Coloring"},"320":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-9","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#donutchart","content":"Just a reminder that `piechart` returns an SVG, so you'll want to add it to the DOM."},"321":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-10","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#quick-start","content":"The most basic possible usage:"},"322":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-11","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#quick-start","content":"colors are given to make the slices visible, but are not required, though\r\nwithout color or stroke colors you'll likely end up with just a circle\r\nvisually!{' '}"},"323":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-12","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#quick-start","content":"Of course it works with different data points too:"},"324":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-13","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#label-options","content":"You can use any string for the `labels` option, and they will be placed in the center of each donut slice."},"325":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-14","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#label-options","content":"Coloring is done via `labelColors`, which takes an array of colors that correspond to the labels. If not provided, the labels will default to white."},"326":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-15","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#data-labels","content":"Or you can use the `dataLabels` option to show the data values instead of custom labels:"},"327":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-16","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#data-labels","content":"`labelColors` also is used to color `dataLabels`.{' '}"},"328":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-17","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#data-labels","content":"The `dataLabels` option also accept `\"percentage\"`:"},"329":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-18","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#center-label","content":"The `centerLabel` option allows you to place a label in the center of the donut chart, which can be used to show a title or other value."},"330":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-19","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#center-label","content":"If you set the `centerLabel` option to `\"sum\"` the center label will show the sum of the data values:"},"331":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-20","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#center-label","content":"**Adjusting center label styles**"},"332":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-21","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#center-label","content":"There are a couple options that allow for adjustment of common title text styles for the center label."},"333":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-22","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#center-label","content":"`centerLabelFontSize`"},"334":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-23","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#center-label","content":"defaults to `32`"},"335":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-24","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#center-label","content":"`centerLabelFontWeight`"},"336":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-25","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#center-label","content":"defaults to `bold`"},"337":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-26","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#center-label","content":"`centerLabelFontFamily`"},"338":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-27","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#center-label","content":"defaults to `monospace`"},"339":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-28","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#center-label","content":"The `centerLabel` will also get a class applied by default that you can use to override the default styling - `\"tmc-pie-center-label\"`."},"340":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-29","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#center-label","content":"You can also use the `centerLabelClass` option to add your own class to the center label `<text>` element."},"341":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-30","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#styling","content":"While styling many options is easily achievable with CSS, there are various styling options available for quick & easy use."},"342":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-31","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#size--spacing","content":"The `size` option will change the size of the chart. By default the `size` is `300` which creates a `300px` square, note that all donut charts are squares!"},"343":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-32","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#size--spacing","content":"You can also change the `padding` which is the interior spacing from the SVG edges to the donut chart itself."},"344":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-33","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#size--spacing","content":"Note that currently `padding` is used uniformly on all sides."},"345":{"id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples-34","page_id":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/donutchart-examples#coloring","content":"While `fillColors` is the way to color each slice, you can also set `strokeColors`, and `strokeWidths` to customize the stroke of each slice."},"346":{"id":"/docs/exampl