a aside!"},"414":{"id":"/docs/examples/linechart-examples-31","page_id":"/docs/examples/linechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/linechart-examples#animejs","content":"And the code:"},"415":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","type":"page","content":"Piechart Examples","breadcrumbs":["The Lib","Usage","Charts Examples"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples"},"416":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-0","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","content":"Let's get cooking!"},"417":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-1","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#piechart","content":"`piechart`"},"418":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-2","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#quick-start","content":"Quick Start"},"419":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-3","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#label-options","content":"Label Options"},"420":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-4","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#data-labels","content":"Data Labels"},"421":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-5","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#center-label","content":"Center Label"},"422":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-6","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#styling","content":"Styling"},"423":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-7","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#size--spacing","content":"Size & Spacing"},"424":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-8","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#coloring","content":"Coloring"},"425":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-9","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#piechart","content":"Just a reminder that `piechart` returns an SVG, so you'll want to add it to the DOM."},"426":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-10","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#quick-start","content":"The most basic possible usage:"},"427":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-11","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#quick-start","content":"colors are given to make the slices visible, but are not required, though\r\nwithout color or stroke colors you'll likely end up with just a circle\r\nvisually!{' '}"},"428":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-12","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#quick-start","content":"Of course it works with different data points too:"},"429":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-13","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#label-options","content":"You can use any string for the `labels` option, and they will be placed in the center of each pie slice."},"430":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-14","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#label-options","content":"Coloring is done via `labelColors`, which takes an array of colors that correspond to the labels. If not provided, the labels will default to white."},"431":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-15","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#data-labels","content":"Or you can use the `dataLabels` option to show the data values instead of custom labels:"},"432":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-16","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#data-labels","content":"`labelColors` also is used to color `dataLabels`.{' '}"},"433":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-17","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#data-labels","content":"The `dataLabels` option also accept `\"percentage\"`:"},"434":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-18","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#center-label","content":"The `centerLabel` option allows you to place a label in the center of the pie chart, which can be used to show a title or other value."},"435":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-19","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#center-label","content":"If you set the `centerLabel` option to `\"sum\"` the center label will show the sum of the data values:"},"436":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-20","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#center-label","content":"**Adjusting center label styles**"},"437":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-21","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#center-label","content":"There are a couple options that allow for adjustment of common title text styles for the center label."},"438":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-22","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#center-label","content":"`centerLabelFontSize`"},"439":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-23","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#center-label","content":"defaults to `32`"},"440":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-24","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#center-label","content":"`centerLabelFontWeight`"},"441":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-25","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#center-label","content":"defaults to `bold`"},"442":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-26","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#center-label","content":"`centerLabelFontFamily`"},"443":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-27","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#center-label","content":"defaults to `monospace`"},"444":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-28","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#center-label","content":"The `centerLabel` will also get a class applied by default that you can use to override the default styling - `\"tmc-pie-center-label\"`."},"445":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-29","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#center-label","content":"You can also use the `centerLabelClass` option to add your own class to the center label `<text>` element."},"446":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-30","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#styling","content":"While styling many options is easily achievable with CSS, there are various styling options available for quick & easy use."},"447":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-31","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#size--spacing","content":"The `size` option will change the size of the chart. By default the `size` is `300` which creates a `300px` square, note that all pie charts are squares!"},"448":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-32","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#size--spacing","content":"You can also change the `padding` which is the interior spacing from the SVG edges to the pie chart itself."},"449":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-33","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#size--spacing","content":"Note that currently `padding` is used uniformly on all sides."},"450":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-34","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#coloring","content":"While `fillColors` is the way to color each slice, you can also set `strokeColors`, and `strokeWidths` to customize the stroke of each slice."},"451":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-35","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#coloring","content":"If you want them all to be uniform, simply provide a single value for each option."},"452":{"id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples-36","page_id":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/examples/piechart-examples#coloring","content":"Additionally, just like other chart types, gradient fills are supported!"},"453":{"id":"/docs/guides/chart-classes","page_id":"/docs/guides/chart-classes","type":"page","content":"Charts Classes","breadcrumbs":["The Lib","Usage","Guides"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/guides/chart-classes"},"454":{"id":"/docs/guides/chart-classes-0","page_id":"/docs/guides/chart-classes","tags":[],"type"